<p>The long-form content pattern is designed to be used repetitively with a variety of
options to achieve an engaging, story-telling experience that still remains
consistent in look and feel. It is ideally suited to blend longer passages of
text with images, video and audio. It also carries several sub-patterns.</p>

<ul>
	<li>Use a University header and University footer (an abbreviated footer
        is typically acceptable).</li>
    <li>Use as many long-form content sections as you want in between.</li>
    <li>At the end of the story narrative, you should use the end piece
    element to communicate that the story has finished.</li>
    <li>The page <strong>must</strong> end with a credits variant, see below.</li>
</ul>

<p>Examples for individual options and sub-patterns are below, but you can
also see the <a href="../../examples/long-form-content.html">full page example
</a> to get a sense for how to use the options and sub-patterns together.</p>


<h2>Options</h2>

<p>You can mix and match these options to get a variety of display options.</p>

<h3>Text and backgrounds</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Black and white</strong> (default)<br>
        By default the background is white and the text is black (dark grey).
    </li>
    <li><strong>Inverse text</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--inverse</code><br>
        This switches the text colour from black to white. It is useful in
        conjunction with a darker background image.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Background image</strong><br>
        Using a <code>style</code> attribute, set the URL of a background image
        on the <code>&lt;section class="long-form"&gt;</code> element.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Background light grey</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--bg-light-grey</code><br>
        Sets the background colour to a light grey.
        </li>
    <li><strong>Darkened background image</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--bg-darken</code><br>
        Adds a semi-transparent black overlay on the background image.
        Typically used to make a bright background image usable behind white
        text.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Lightened background image</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--bg-lighten</code><br>
        Adds a semi-transparent white overlay on the background image.
        Typically used to make a dark background image usable behind black
        text.
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Width</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Compressed content column</strong> (default)<br>
        By default content has a width of 8 grid columns with a 2 grid column
        offset achieving a 2-8-2 pattern.</li>
    <li><strong>Medium content column</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--width-medium</code><br>
        This sets the content to have a width of 10 grid columns with a 1
        grid column offset achieving a 1-10-1 pattern.
    </li>
    <li><strong>Full-width content column</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--width-full</code><br>
        This sets the content to span all 12 grid columns.
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Vertical padding</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Vertical padding</strong> (default)<br>
        By default there is generous padding on the top and bottom.
    </li>
    <li><strong>No vertical padding</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--padding-none</code><br>
        Removes the top and bottom padding.
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Credits</h3>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Credits section</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.long-form--credits</code><br>
        All long-form content pages must end with a credits section. This section has a medium (1-10-1) width, grey background, smaller text, and a St&nbsp;Andrews logo in a watermark effect.
    </li>
</ul>

